theorem P2_union {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A → Topology.P2 B → Topology.P2 (A ∪ B) := by
  intro hA hB
  dsimp [Topology.P2] at hA hB ⊢
  intro x hx
  cases hx with
  | inl hAx =>
      have hxA : x ∈ interior (closure (interior A)) := hA hAx
      have hsubsetA : interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆
          interior (closure (interior (A ∪ B))) := by
        have hinterA : interior A ⊆ interior (A ∪ B) := by
          apply interior_mono
          exact Set.subset_union_left _ _
        have hclA : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (A ∪ B)) :=
          closure_mono hinterA
        exact interior_mono hclA
      exact hsubsetA hxA
  | inr hBx =>
      have hxB : x ∈ interior (closure (interior B)) := hB hBx
      have hsubsetB : interior (closure (interior B)) ⊆
          interior (closure (interior (A ∪ B))) := by
        have hinterB : interior B ⊆ interior (A ∪ B) := by
          apply interior_mono
          exact Set.subset_union_right _ _
        have hclB : closure (interior B) ⊆ closure (interior (A ∪ B)) :=
          closure_mono hinterB
        exact interior_mono hclB
      exact hsubsetB hxB

theorem P3_of_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    Topology.P3 A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  have h : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
    apply interior_mono
    exact subset_closure
  simpa [hA.interior_eq] using h
